      "text": [
        ": قُلْتُ لِأَبِی عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ع قَدْ وَطَّنْتُ نَفْسِی عَلَی لُزُومِ الْحَجِّ کُلَّ عَامٍ بِنَفْسِی أَوْ بِرَجُلٍ مِنْ أَهْلِ بَیْتِی بِمَالِی فَقَالَ وَ قَدْ عَزَمْتَ عَلَی ذَلِکَ قُلْتُ نَعَمْ قَالَ فَإِنْ فَعَلْتَ ذَلِکَ فَأَیْقِنْ بِکَثْرَهِ الْمَالِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
          "4. And it was narrated to me by Muhammad b. al-Hassan (rah) from Muhammad b. al-Hassan al-Saffar from al-Abbas b. Ma’ruf from Ali b. Mahziyar from Hamad b. Isa from Yahya b. Umar from Ishaq b. Ammar who said: “If that is so, you should remain assured that you will get excessive wealth. Glad tiding to you for excessive wealth.”"
        ]
